  "description": "Markdown is a lightweight markup language. It is also, read as a semiotic system, a medium that makes the structure of meaning visible and machine-traversable. This lesson examines why plain text with minimal markup is an effective substrate for knowledge work — what properties it has, what it makes possible, and what it costs.\n¶Plain text as durable substrate A markdown file is a plain text file. This is a constraint with structural consequences:\n",
